		Danuta: No… that’s not what I said… Frankly Zdzichu might be in no shape to travel…
- CHECK COMPASS
	You pull a compass out of your pocket, that you had the forethought to bring. This way you’ll get your bearings and save time.
	Bezi: [i]So the camp was east of the village. I've run more or less south to distract them, since the pole is north.[/i]
	Bezi: [i]If I go west/northwest I should reach the village.[/i]
	You keep heading in that direction, but find no village and the sun has set.
	Bezi: [i]Did I overshoot it?[/i]
	You try to adjust, but still nothing and soon enough the light from your torchlight attracts attention. You’ve been found by the soldiers!
	You once again break into a sprint, turning off your flashlight, but in the complete darkness you trip and fall over some roots.
	The soldiers catch up to you and you are shot in the back.
